Concern: a deterministic, offline CLI/MCP server that maps any workspace as an annotated tree plus cross-ecosystem dependency graph, enforces the first-line annotation format (strict-check), and teaches it (guide shown in --help and on a failing check), so an agent routes a codebase without reading it | Non-concern: judging what the annotations mean (true? belongs? dead? the agent decides, the tool only renders and format-checks); running the target's build, tests, network, or model calls; writing or fixing the annotations | IO: (workspace root, config) -> map or strict-check verdict
